This paper deals with sentiment classification, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP). The use of tree-structured Long Short-Term Memory (LSTM) with an attention mechanism is a common technique in NLP, and thus the paper is likely to be categorized under cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the use of machine learning algorithms for sentiment classification makes it relevant to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of LSTM also suggests that the paper may be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper deals with text classification, which is a common task in information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible category as well.
